<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-300-201  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 300 201  OV: 09 299 257.andM; </DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  August 20 1990 v7 n33 p89(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software Ventures Corp.: MicroPhone II 3.0. (Software Review) (oneof four evaluations of communications software in 'Auto-scriptingspurs Mac communication') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bethoney, Herb; Schroeder, Erica.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Software Ventures Corp's $295 Microphone II 3.0 communicationssoftware for the Apple Macintosh uses one of the most powerfulscripting language available and is easy to use.andP;  All scriptingcommands are available in a scrollable list and a turnkey featurepermits a user to specify a script to perform on startup andquitting.andP;  The new communications software allows scripts to befully automated from the start of a session to the end and anoption permits the script to be hidden.andP;  MicroPhone II comes withautomated scripts for many on-line services including BIX,Compuserve, Delphi, GEnie, Dow Jones, EasyLink, MCI Mail and theWell.andP;  The new software's interface uses graphics well and does anexcellent job with file transfers.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software Ventures Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)MicroPhone II 3.0 (Communications software).andO;Topic:     Communications SoftwareEvaluationSoftware PackagesSoftware Publishers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Software Ventures Corp.andM;MICROPHONE II 3.0andM;With one of the most powerful scripting languages available, MicroPhone is atthe same time easy-to-use.andM;Its Watch Me feature automatically builds scripts by watching the user'sinteraction with another computer system, and scripts can be modified byusing the script editor.andP;  This feature makes all the scripting commandsavailable in a scrollable list, and a turnkey feature permits a user tospecify a script to perform on startup and quitting.andM;As a result, a script can be fully automated from the start of a session tothe end.andP;  An option permits the script to be hidden, keeping the nuts andbolts of a script in the background and allowing the script maker to presenta polished telecommunications application to the user.andM;MicroPhone II 3.0 comes with automated scripts for many on-line services:BIX, Compuserve, Delphi, GEnie, Dow Jones, EasyLink, MCI Mail and the Well.andM;MicroPhone II also comes with Dialoger for MicroPhone, a HyperCard stack thatallows creation of dialogue boxes, complete with pop-up menus and scrollinglists that can be part of scripts.andP;  MicroPhone II's scripting language alsosupports the XCMD and XFCN commands used in HyperCard so scripts can makecalls to other programs that support external commands and functions.andM;MicroPhone II's interface uses graphics well.andP;  For example, there are smallicons at the bottom of the main window for halting and resuming the flow oftext, for stopping scripts, and for controlling a built-in combination clock,calendar and stopwatch.andP;  Scripts can be represented as buttons or icons.andM;Script tracing and debugging is also displayed in this area of the window.andP;  Asplit-screen feature can be used to allow replies to messages inon-line-service scripts.andP;  MicroPhone II comes with a user's guide, referencemanual and a guide to resources and utilities.andM;MicroPhone II does an excellent job with file transfers.andP;  Its support of theZmodem protocol lets interrupted transfers resume at the point of failure andoffers improved throughput over other protocols.andP;  An XCMD that supportsCompuServe's QuickB protocol is also provided.andM;Software Ventures Corp. of Berkeley, Calif., can be reached at (415)644-3232.andM;----------Buyers say .andP;  .  .andM;For Karen Thomas, microcomputer evaluation specialist for Martin MariettaCorp. in Chantilly, Va., some of the significant factors in choosingMicroPhone II were the user interface and the size, type and range ofcustomized file-transfer capabilities.andM;She was also pleased to have extra features such as the Ymodem and Kermitprotocols, as well as good technical support and error-handling capabilities.andM;The only improvements that MicroPhone II needs are support for more thaneight colors and 3270 emulation, according to Thomas.andM;&quot;Our users just take all things they want to send into a single folder, clickon it, open an icon, then go out for a cup of coffee, come back and it'sdone,&quot; said Bill Cook, technical adviser for Pitney Bowes Inc., anoffice-equipment manufacturer in Norwalk, Conn.andM;&quot;It's the most flexible, most powerful communications package on any platformI've seen,&quot; he added.andP;  &quot;It has a programming language that will eitherautomate tasks or do anything you need to do.andP;  Short of writing your own[scripts], you can't do any better.&quot;andM;&quot;I can write a script that does the first 99.5 percent of the work for users.andO;You can make typical tasks look very simple to the user,&quot; he said.andP;  &quot;I likethe ability to write fully customized communication programs.andP;  I can transferresults to the central computer with out bothering the user.&quot; MicroPhone IIdoes not pretend to be a DEC emulator, said Cook.andP;  But, &quot;you can add functionkey functionality through scripting,&quot; he said.andO;</TEXT></DOC>